@Git Center: You have a `signAndPublish` function, but then you also have a `sign` function (in repo.js):
```
sign() {
		return this.zeroPage.cmd("siteSign", {inner_path: "merged-GitCenter/" + this.address + "/content.json"})
			.then(res => {
				if(res != "ok") {
					return Promise.reject(res);
				}
			});
	}
```
But this one doesn't have the private key argument. I don't know if this is right or wrong or if it even matters. I'm just trying to find *something* that might make this act weird.

